<subSubSection id="48D355CA8FFBFE7548F75180FBBFF917" pageId="437" pageNumber="438" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="007606418FFBFE7548F75180FBBFF917" blockId="437.[151,1436,1671,1768]" pageId="437" pageNumber="438">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FFBFE7548F75180FE9EF934" bold="true" box="[199,315,1708,1732]" pageId="437" pageNumber="438">Remarks.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus id="DF72B8E38FFBFE7549455180FE00F934" box="[373,421,1708,1732]" pageId="437" pageNumber="438">type</typeStatus>
seems to be lost. The original description is so incomplete, that it is impossible to include 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28FFBFE7548A751FDFEABF918" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1914" box="[151,270,1744,1768]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Lestodryinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="437" pageNumber="438" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perkinsi">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FFBFE7548A751FDFEABF918" box="[151,270,1744,1768]" italics="true" pageId="437" pageNumber="438">L. perkinsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the key to the 
<collectingRegion id="C20DC8A38FFBFE7549E151E3FD88F917" box="[465,557,1743,1767]" country="Democratic Republic of the Congo" name="Orientale" pageId="437" pageNumber="438">Oriental</collectingRegion>
species. Probably it is a species of 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28FFBFE754B8851FCFBB7F917" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1804" box="[952,1042,1744,1767]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Dryinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="437" pageNumber="438" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FFBFE754B8851FCFBB7F917" box="[952,1042,1744,1767]" italics="true" pageId="437" pageNumber="438">Dryinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
